The paper discusses wearable sensors and their applications in health monitoring, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of wireless body area networks (WBANs) also suggests a possible fit for the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) category. The discussion of noise removing filters could also potentially fit under signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions non-medical applications such as daily exercise monitoring and motion detection, which could fall under the categories of other computer science (cs.OH) or computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CY).
